<BaseLayout
  title="Financing your CORELOT home"
  description="Construction-to-permanent loan guidance, budget components, and trusted lender partners for on-your-lot builds in Virginia."
  canonicalPath="/financing"
>
  <header class="page-header">
    <p class="pill">Financing</p>
    <h1>Understanding construction-to-permanent financing.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Building on your lot requires different financing than buying a finished home. Here's what you need to know about construction-perm loans, budget ranges, and working with lenders who understand the on-your-lot build process.</p>
  </header>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>The CORELOT Process - Design Retainer First</h2>
    <p>Before approaching lenders, we start with a <strong>design retainer</strong> to ensure you have full approval on your plan and budget. This protects you from moving forward with financing before knowing your true project cost.</p>

    <div class="feature-box">
      <h3>What the Design Retainer Covers:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Complete plan review and customization discussion</li>
        <li>Structural options and modifications specific to your needs</li>
        <li>Site-specific feasibility assessment (grading, utilities, access)</li>
        <li>Detailed line-item budget including all site work variables</li>
        <li>Preliminary timeline based on your lot and plan selection</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <p><strong>Why This Matters for Financing:</strong> Lenders need accurate numbers. By completing the design phase first, you'll approach lenders with a finalized plan, real site work costs based on your actual lot conditions, and no surprises about what the project will truly cost.</p>

    <p class="highlight">Once design is approved and you have firm numbers, you're ready to seek financing with realistic expectations.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>How Construction-Perm Loans Work</h2>
    <p>Most on-your-lot builds use a <strong>construction-to-permanent loan</strong> (often called a "one-time close" loan). This combines construction financing and your long-term mortgage into a single loan, which means:</p>

    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>One closing</strong> instead of two (saves time and closing costs)</li>
          <li><strong>One set of closing costs</strong> instead of paying twice</li>
          <li><strong>Rate lock protection</strong> during construction (typically 12-18 months)</li>
          <li><strong>Automatic conversion</strong> to permanent mortgage when construction completes</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="info-box">
        <h4>During Construction:</h4>
        <p>You make interest-only payments on funds already drawn. The lender releases money in scheduled "draws" as work progresses. An inspector verifies completion before each draw.</p>
        <p><strong>Typical draw schedule:</strong> foundation, framing, dried-in, mechanicals, finishes, final</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p><strong>After Construction:</strong> Loan converts to a standard 15- or 30-year mortgage with monthly payments that include principal and interest. No refinancing needed.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>Budget Components</h2>
    <p>A complete on-your-lot budget includes more than just the house. <strong>Plans are priced, but site work is the variable</strong> that changes dramatically by lot.</p>

    <div class="budget-grid">
      <div class="budget-category">
        <h3>Land Costs</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Purchase price (if not already owned)</li>
          <li>Survey and title work: $1,500â€“$3,000</li>
          <li>Soil tests and perc testing: $800â€“$2,500</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="budget-category highlight-category">
        <h3>Site Preparation (The Variable)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Clearing and grading: $5,000â€“$40,000+ (depends on terrain, tree removal, rock)</li>
          <li>Driveway installation: $3,000â€“$20,000+ (length, material, base requirements)</li>
          <li>Well and septic (if needed): $15,000â€“$35,000+ (depth, system type, field size)</li>
          <li>Utility connections: $2,000â€“$15,000 (distance from street, easements)</li>
          <li>Retaining walls or special drainage: varies significantly</li>
          <li>Erosion control and stormwater management: lot-specific</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="budget-category">
        <h3>Plan Package & Modifications</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Base plan purchase: priced per plan</li>
          <li>Plan modifications or customizations: quoted during design retainer</li>
          <li>Structural engineering (if required): $1,500â€“$5,000</li>
          <li>Permit and plan review fees: $2,000â€“$8,000</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="budget-category">
        <h3>House Construction</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Foundation: $25,000â€“$50,000</li>
          <li>Framing and structure: $40,000â€“$85,000</li>
          <li>Mechanical systems: $35,000â€“$65,000</li>
          <li>Interior finishes: $30,000â€“$75,000</li>
          <li>Exterior finishes: $15,000â€“$40,000</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="example-budgets">
      <h3>Example Budget Ranges (Northern Virginia):</h3>
      <div class="budget-examples">
        <div class="budget-example">
          <strong>1,800 sqft ranch on level lot with utilities</strong>
          <span class="budget-range">$280,000â€“$350,000 total project</span>
        </div>
        <div class="budget-example">
          <strong>2,400 sqft two-story on sloped lot requiring grading</strong>
          <span class="budget-range">$375,000â€“$475,000 total project</span>
        </div>
        <div class="budget-example">
          <strong>2,800 sqft on wooded acreage with well/septic</strong>
          <span class="budget-range">$450,000â€“$575,000 total project</span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="note">These are rough ranges. Your design retainer process will produce an accurate budget based on your actual lot conditions and plan selection.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section">
    <h2>The CORELOT Financing Timeline</h2>

    <div class="timeline">
      <div class="timeline-step">
        <div class="step-number">1</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Design Retainer & Budget Development</h3>
          <p>We start hereâ€”before you talk to any lenders:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Review your lot conditions (topography, utilities, access)</li>
            <li>Finalize plan selection and any modifications</li>
            <li>Obtain site work estimates from our trade partners</li>
            <li>Build detailed line-item budget with contingencies</li>
            <li>Complete feasibility confirmation</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="timeline-duration">Timeline: 2-3 weeks typically</p>
          <p class="why-box"><strong>Why This Protects You:</strong> You'll know the real cost before committing to a lender. Plans are priced; we're determining the site variables and any plan updates you need.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-step">
        <div class="step-number">2</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Lender Selection & Pre-Approval</h3>
          <p>Armed with your budget, you're ready to approach lenders. We provide builder credentials, construction timeline, budget breakdown, and comparable sales data for the appraiser.</p>
          <p class="timeline-duration">Timeline: 2-4 weeks typically</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-step">
        <div class="step-number">3</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Loan Commitment & Closing</h3>
          <p>Lender issues commitment, title prepares documents, and you close with your rate locked for the construction period.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-step">
        <div class="step-number">4</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Construction Draws</h3>
          <p>We notify the lender at each milestone (foundation, framing, mechanicals, finishes, final). Inspector verifies, funds release within 3-5 business days.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline-step">
        <div class="step-number">5</div>
        <div class="step-content">
          <h3>Conversion to Permanent</h3>
          <p>At completion, your loan automatically converts to a standard mortgage. No refinancing needed.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content-section lenders-section">
    <h2>Trusted Lender Partners</h2>
    <p>We work with construction-perm specialists who understand on-your-lot builds and the CORELOT process. You're free to use any lender, but these partners have closed multiple projects with our clients:</p>

    <div class="lenders-grid">
      <div class="lender-card">
        <h3>Fairway Independent Mortgage</h3>
        <div class="lender-contacts">
          <div class="contact">
            <strong>Scott Hine</strong>
